@kjozsa are you sure this is the right way to approach this security vulnerability? I mean if Fineract is being put behind a CDN/LB, the remote IP address will not be the actual client address but the CDN/LB's address. 

How about just enforcing Fineract to use BCrypt with a minimum 8 characters, symbols, letters (upper,lowercase) and numbers as passwords? 

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ed79bb96-e77c-4a05-8a32-4c49164c4f39)

@janez89 Can you please attach some related test cases?
- Set value on loan product, fetch value from loan product
- Loan inherit it from loan product, fetch value from loan... etc
